gram\": \"the Olympic men's pommel competition\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bercy Arena inParis\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whitlock was one of a record-breaking number of eightBritishmale gymnasts to seal their places in individual finals on Saturday, withJake Jarmanand Luke Whitehouse through on floor, Harry Hepworth on rings, Hepworth and Jarman on vault, and Jarman and Joe Fraser in the all-around.\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1701128262398966e-38, \"text\": \"Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}, {\"begin\": 745, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\", \"score\": 0.9999999999881766, \"rank\": 1.1929338039795584e-11, \"text\": \"Hepworth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a record-breaking number\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 582}, {\"ngram\": \"eightBritishmale gymnasts\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"their places\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 632}, {\"ngram\": \"individual finals\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 653}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 665}, {\"ngram\": \"floor\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"rings\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"Jarman\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"vault\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-around\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The respective successes of Hepworth and Jarman also mean it will be the first time in history thatGreat Britainhas been represented in either a vault or rings final at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\", \"score\": 0.9999999999881766, \"rank\": 1.1929338039795584e-11, \"text\": \"Hepworth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Hepworth\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The respective successes\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 845}, {\"ngram\": \"Jarman\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 868}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"thatGreat\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"Britainhas\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"either a vault\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"rings\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 980}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1002}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whitlock, who is competing at his last Games, scored 15.166, placing him second behind Stephen Nedoroscik of the US after the first qualifying rotation, a result that means his place in next Saturday's eight-man apparatus final is effectively assured.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1092, \"end\": 1110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Nedoroscik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\"}, {\"begin\": 1118, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.7860695837913602, \"rank\": 0.27090378204292564, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Whitlock\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"his last Games\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1049}, {\"ngram\": \"the first qualifying rotation\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1156}, {\"ngram\": \"his place\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1187}, {\"ngram\": \"next Saturday's eight-man apparatus final\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 31-year-old, who won the pommel title in both 2016 and 2020 but has struggled with injury since reversing a retirement decision in the wake of his success in Tokyo, believes he is still capable of plenty of improvements.\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999942667728, \"rank\": 5.731109218248453e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pommel title\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"injury\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"a retirement decision\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"the wake\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"his success\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"improvements\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The relief is crazy,\\\" admitted Whitlock, who also did his bit to help the team with routines on horizontal and parallel bars.\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1516, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1701128262398966e-38, \"text\": \"Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}], \"nou